text: The 1756 English cricket season was the 13th season following the earliest known codification of the Laws of Cricket. Details have survived of five eleven-a-side matches between significant teams, including three involving Hambledon teams. ==Matches== Five eleven-a-side matches between significant teams are known to have taken place.ACS, p.22.Other matches in England 1756, CricketArchive.
